    "The former puts conditions on the variables that must be satisfied, whereas violating the latter merely imposes a penalty on the cost function.",
    "There exists a variety of constraints that are considered in the literature on assortment optimization.",
    "They are briefly introduced in the following.",
    "• The cardinality constraint limits the total size of the offered assortment to a maximum of C options; more formally ∑ i∈N x i ≤ C.",
    "To avoid trivial cases, typically C ≤ n is assumed."
